Executive Profile
Ronald   Lalla  Executive Vice President of Merchandising, Office Depot International (UK) LimitedAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 5 different industries.59--
Background

		Mr. Ronald Lalla, also known as Ron, has been an Executive Vice President of Merchandising at Office Depot International (UK) Limited since December 2013. Mr. Lalla served as an Executive Vice President and Chief Merchandising Officer at Office Depot, Inc. since December 2013 until March 23, 2017. He was responsible for defining the overall Merchandising category and assortment strategy and strengthening market position and brand recognition through innovative product ... development and strategic vendor relationships. He served as the Chief Merchandising Officer and Executive Vice President of OfficeMax Incorporated since March 19, 2012. He has extensive retail merchandising and business-to-business experience. He served as the Chief Merchandising Officer and Chief Technology Officer for Katz Group. He served as an Executive Vice President of Merchandising at Katz Group Pharmacies Inc. (Alternative Name: The Katz Group of Companies Inc.) since January 2009. Prior to that, he served as an Executive Vice President of Global Merchandising of Corporate Express N.V. since January 1, 2006. He served as Vice President of Merchandising U.S. within Buhrmann NV's subsidiary Corporate Express North America since January, 2003. Prior to Buhrmann, he served as in various management positions within K-Mart and in public accounting within PricewaterhouseCoopers. He spent more than 10 years at Kmart Corporation, where he held several leadership positions of increasing responsibility in merchandising, store operations and finance, including Director of Finance, International Operations and Senior Vice President, Global Operations. He served as a Board Member of Wellspring in Canada. Mr. Lalla attended the University of Manitoba, where he received his Bachelor’s Degree in Commerce and then later earned his MBA from Duke University.Read Full Background




