OfficeMax names Ronald Lalla new chief merchandising officer


OfficeMax Inc. announced today that it has named Ronald Lalla executive vice president and chief merchandising officer, effective next Monday, March 19.In this role, Mr. Lalla will have responsibility for all aspects of the Naperville-based office-products retailer's merchandising, including category management, strategic product planning, global sourcing, and private-label expansion.Most recently, he served as chief merchandising officer and chief technology officer for Katz Group, a Canadian drug store operator with more than 1,800 stores. Before that, he was executive vice president of global merchandising for Corporate Express, a Dutch company that supplies office products to businesses and institutions and was acquired by Staples Inc. in 2008.  He also held leadership positions in merchandising, store operations and finance during more than 10 years at Troy, Mich.-based Kmart Corp.OfficeMax is in the midst of a turnaround effort: The retail chain laid out plans for improvements during an investor presentation in November.Mr. Lalla attended the University of Manitoba, where he received a degree in Commerce, and earned an M.B.A. from Duke University.


OfficeMax Inc.
Retail and Sales



























